caption: OMG so good! Definitely a win for restaurant week to go there. Tried a lot between the two of us. Everything was unbelievably yummy. Great wine selection also! I'll be back often.
Excellent food, services and plentiful portions! Drink were kick azz!
Love Pacino's, food is well done and the atmosphere is fantastic. Definitely will be back!

caption: Amazing food and even better service!
The food was Amazing and atmosphere was beautiful.  I truly enjoyed this restaurant!

This was our first time dining at Pacino's, but it will definitely not be our last.  Everything on the menu was appealing and made choosing quite difficult, but all four people in our party were totally pleased with our orders.  We loved our entrees, the warm bread with olive oil & parmesan and our desserts (Tiramisu and Triple Chocolate Mousse).  The wine choices and cocktails were perfect as well.  The ambience of the restaurant was also upscale yet intimate & relaxing.  I can't neglect to mention our waiter (Jack B).  He was both engaging and attentive to our needs.  We look forward to returning and will definitely ask for him again.  Thank you for a superb dining experience and enjoyable evening!
I love eating at Pacino’s. The food is excellent and the value is incredible.
Great food and prices!!  We came late and they were more than welcoming to us, definitely recommend!
Friendly server. Delicious food. We had the bucatini bolognese and spaghetti carbonara. Highly recommended.
The food, the atmosphere,  the staff, everything here made this the perfect Halloween
Great food and great service!

Food was decent, but the service was horrible. We were basically pushed out the door and told it was closing time. Our server essentially told us she was the last one left and the restaurant had closed, trying to guilt trip up. It was 8:45 and the restaurant closed at 9 🙄. That really spoiled the special occasion we were there for. Would not recommend.
We really try to be understanding during the pandemic but our order was absolutely terrible.  Soggy pasta, wrong entree, seafood with no flavor, bland marinara.. far too pricey for quality received.

Came here a few months ago and the caio e pepe was served in a bowl made of crusted parmesan which was fantastic! Of course they removed the parmesan bowl from the cacio e pepe dish and now  the $17 entree is so NOT WORTH IT!
Clean foods great great service. I was her with a group of friends and we are 20ish. They treated us with respect
Everything we had was delicious. Also, the outdoor seating that's actually far enough apart for effective social distancing!

The restaurant was beautiful and clean along with great care and service. Our server was kind and helpful always around to take our order and to check up on our table. There are many selections to choose from with such great qualities. Excellent appetizers, main courses, and desserts. I highly recommend everyone to go.

AMAZING food! I think quite possibly the best Italian food I’ve ever had. However I’m giving 4 stars instead of 5 because the wait staff seemed to completely forget about me and we were waiting for 30 minutes before anyone took our order.
A place we just found, sooo good. A must try, we will be back.
Excellent home made food from scratch
Great good

After a long day of gardening, a long week of work, and a seemingly racing past summer, it was time to venture out. We made the decision that it was absolutely necessary to really go out. Put on your heels, a nice shirt, those dangly earrings you got on vacation, and go. We also decided to treat the parents, who are equally due for a night out. We came across Pacino's by happenstance, but it was a chance encounter that felt like everything had just lined up. We lucked out with a table inside as it was a bit cold out and were instantly greeted. The menu is diverse and easy to read, so we got to decide on a bottle of Moscato, grilled calamari, and a Limoncello Martini to start. The grilled calamari was done to perfection, fork-soft and a perfect balance between buttery and smoky. The drinks came out quickly and the table bread was crispy on the outside, pillowy on the inside. All off to a wonderful start. For entrees, we decided on veal Parmesan, chicken Parmesan,  pappardelle with tomato-cream sauce with sausage, and linguine mediterraneo. High marks all around, everything was delicious. For dessert, the easy choice was tiramisu, which was remarked around the table as the best we'd ever had. The owner was very kind to thank us for coming, which was a very nice touch. We will certainly be back.
Great service!
Incredible take out. Looking forward to the dine-in experience!
Love this restaurant! great food, great ambiance, great staff. Looking forward to returning soon!

Pacino's is a wonderful addition to the South Loop. We've dined in for pizza and negronis and gotten takeout during the shutdown as well. Everything we've ordered has been superb. The salads are fresh and the pasta is perfectly cooked. Two standout items are the beet carpaccio salad and the linguini nero with tons of tasty fresh seafood.
Always Great!!!! Kitchen....Accomidating Staff........Friendly & Welcoming Food........ Great !!! Pizza some of the best in Chicago !!! Atmosphere.... High End Casual YOU NEED TO BE HERE!!!
Amber was a superb bar tender. Providing entertaining banter as well as checking on the status of my drinks!
The food was amazing! The space is sleek yet warm and cozy. Definitely going back!

Everything was good. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable, the cocktails were potent and flavorful, the service was prompt and the food was delicious. The servings are generous so bring a hearty appetite with you.
Awesome place
Nice and clean.  Waitress very nice!
New favorite south loop Italian place

Good arrabiata sauce! Ask for it spicy and you will get spicy! It's a cozy place walking distance from home and conveniently located to shops and Whole Foods. Good wine selection-if they are not sold out of the bottles! (Which is a good sign!) Friendly staff.

Was really looking forward to going here, however was completely disappointed.  Had the eggplant with spaghetti.  I thought the eggplant tasted like eating rubber,  just awful.   The pasta sauce was tasteless,  like it was just canned tomatoes without any seasoning.   Very disappointed.
Great food

I got a carryout order of lasagna this past Friday.  The meat sauce around the lasagna was delicious.  The lasagna itself left a lot to be desired.  The noodles toward the bottom were tough, as though they were undercooked; and, the meat in the lasagna was bland.
Great food. Service needs a little work, but they're new, so I'll give them a break on that for now. Had two pastas and even if service remains questionable, still worth it! 😀
Amazing food and great service. Will definitely be coming back!
Pretty good ambience, good staff and great food. Rigatoni with Vodka sauce is a must try.
Great place near little Italy that doesn’t cost an arm&leg to eat at. New favorite place in the neighborhood! 🇮🇹

The kitchen saved this place. When we arrived, a busboy brought us bread and water but then not a single person stopped by until we got up to ask the hostess after about 15 min. The dining room was about half full and the table next to us had their order taken  immediately. We were only checked on when our food was delivered and when we asked for the check. The food was decent - I recommend the calamari; however, I'm pretty sure I got beef ravioli rather than the lobster that was ordered.
Good food and service.
taste was lower than average, over priced for the taste, nothing special about this place.
Very authentic!

The interior of the restaurant is spacious with a clean design. Regarding the food, we ordered Buratta, Brussel sprouts, risotto Al Fungi and risotto Pescatore. The Burrata was very disappointing. It consisted of three pieces of cheese, chewy prosciutto and toasted white bread. There was no effort in the presentation, the cheese was tough (maybe it was old, because buratta usually melts in your mouth). The risotto Al Fungi was delicious, the best dish of everything we ordered. The risotto Pescatore was with seafood but the seafood was overcooked/rubbery. The texture of the Brussel sprouts felt like they were steamed, not really baked.

We loved our experience here. High end experience and food for a really good price. Items ranged from $13 for a meal to $47, I felt like there was something for everyone's budget. Owner was very nice, servers were nice, food was AMAZING. They validate parking. We had the sausage and peppers for an appetizer and the sausage is made in house: delicious! I also had the chicken involtino-best I've ever had. The portions are large. Nice for dinner and a movie or dinner and shopping night out.
The brunch Crab meat benedict is great! Service is swift, interior is upscale, and the price is decent!

The linguini with tomato basil sauce was the right consistency and it hugged the noodles perfectly. Had an Argentinian malbec. Tried mama pizza and their deliciously flavored meatballs. A canoli for dessert. Great place to go for a great meal after a long day of shopping or after work meal! Definitely coming back!

Phenomenal food and staff! We've heard amazing things about Pacino's so we had to try it. Right from the start, the hostess was warm and friendly. Everyone we came in contact with was super welcoming and wanted to ensure we had the best experience. Food wise - from the wine to the dessert, we were blown away by how delicious everything was. We can't wait to go back!
The food reminded us of a chain such as Olive Garden. Was not impressed with the quality/taste.

Food is fresh and the flavors are great!  Everyone is super friendly and helpful.  Prices are unbeatable!  And portions are pretty big!  Mussels were cooked to perfection and large, eggplant and chicken parmigiana were just right as well!  Can't wait to try new items.

I spontaneously decided to have dinner here on 11/29/19 before my movie date. The food was delicious, the drinks were well worth the money, and the service was outstanding. I have never taken the time to review a restaurant, but I had to after dining here. I can honestly say that I have never had such a pleasant dining experience. The staff and owner had the most genuine concern about making sure everything was perfect. Our experience here set the mood for a flawless night, which is priceless. If you haven't been here, I highly recommend it.

Food and atmosphere was marvelous, from the floors to the restrooms were spotless!... Management was extraordinary, Tony GM was out on the floor serving tables which made a difference in my experience... first time dining, definitely going back!

We are from the neighborhood and stopped in for Brunch today. My daughter ordered the traditional Eggs Benedict, I ordered the Pacino omelette. According to the menu, the Pacino omelette is made with tomatoes, mozzarella and spinach plus marina. Both dishes were entirely flavorless, there was barely any hollandaise sauce on the eggs benny and what was there was tasteless.  The omelette was made with no spinach, and hardly any cheese, again this dish was flavorless, (see my uploaded picture). The server never even came to ask us how our meal was until we were ready for the check, otherwise I would have mentioned the problem to her. I did mention it to the hostess on the way out. I would never do brunch here again and these guys have some work to do.

Great atmosphere, good for date night. Good service. Good prices. nice, they recently opened so I'm guessing they still need to practice the menu. Burger was dry, pizza was good, eggplant was too chewy and slightly over fryed. Pasta was ok. I would say that the pizza was the best. I will probably try again as they polish the kitchen.
Lovely venue. Open and airy. We had white fish vesuvio with fresh mixed vegetables.  Affordable, great staff.

My daughter and I went to see a movie and just happen to see this new restaurant. It previously was a Mexican restaurant. From the moment we stepped in the door, we were treated with excellent service. The decor is simply beautiful, the atmosphere is calming, the staff was very friendly, and the chef even came out to personally bring us some extra sauce for our dish. Lastly, the food is SUPERB. Authentic Italian seasoning cooked to perfection. The chicken Alfredo and Caesar Salad with chicken....OMG delicious. The cucumber & lemon water was even good...lol. We will definitely be back!!
Really great food, we had the meatballs, chicken Parmesan and chicken Marsala. I would recommend this place to anyone and will definitely be going back!

(Translated by Google) Excellent place to spend a pleasant afternoon delicious food and excellent service.  (Original) Excelente lugar para pasar una tarde agradable comida deliciosa y excelente servicio.
Very nice and food was awesome. Enrique lores was so professional.
High energy, great classic Italian dining!
Great ambience. Great food. Great service!

Loved the atmosphere and decor of this restaurant. Bar is beautiful and rest of the space is very clean, modern. The service was excellent and food was great. We particularly enjoyed the bolognese and carbonara. Will definitely come back!

I had the pleasure of attending Opening night and was so delighted with the atmosphere and management I met, even the busy Chef came out to say Hello to his guests later in the evening.   The food was great and even though not everything went well, I still had a Wonderful evening!!!  I highly recommend dining at this restaurant, it’s beautiful, in a great area, great food, management that cares . . . And for everyone that gave this restaurant a low rating, Please remember, everything and No One is not perfect!!!  Life would boring if we didn’t go through trials and tribulations!!!!  Save a seat at the bar for me, I’m definitely coming back to eat again, can’t wait!!!!!  💋
Outstanding first experience! Great ambience with nice, modern-style decor. The bolognese and burrata were out of this world. Looking forward to my second visit.

Great experience last night at Pacino’s. Not surprised the food was good, the Chef has a great reputation for traditional Italian flavor. The Bolognese was outstanding and always my litmus test for Italian Restaurants. Cool atmosphere as well. If you are having Vino with your meal order a glass of the the Primitivo 👌🏽
Incredible experience, ambiance was beautiful, staff was very professional, and the food was incredible.  I could eat the meatballs every day!

Opening night was a complete disaster. There was something wrong with every course of our meal. The wine we ordered is not what we received, and they tried to charge us two times the price for the wrong wine. They brought us the wrong appetizer, the sausage rigatoni pasta was meatless, and the pizza was completely raw and doughy. My pasta was cold, and the server was nowhere to be found. The whole experience lasted 2 1/2 hours because they were so backed up. Will never be returning.

Opening night event...the service, food and overall evening left so much more to be desired. Undercooked food, inattentive staff and bad vibes ruined what should have been a perfect celebration.  I’d give this place a few months to work out the kinks and hopefully replace the manager before coming here.  Yikes!

Had a great experience on their opening night. Would certainly come back!  Positives: great service, tasty food, large but cohesive menu, classy and contemporary atmosphere, and very reasonable prices.  Suggestions: vegetables were perfectly cooked, but a bit under seasoned.
